---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
import whiterabbit from '../assets/whiterabbit.png';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />

    <main class="container padding-large">

      <h1 class="text-center paper">Dioni Zhong</h1>

      <p class="paper">
        Storyteller trapped in a programmer's body.
        <br />Worked on movies and video games in my past lives. Yes, you know the movies. Maybe not the games.
        <br />Two Bachelor degrees — Software Engineering and English Literature & Creative Writing.
        <br />One funded my entire life. One did not. Guess which is which.
        <br />Lived in 7 different countries, 9 cities. Perpetual chronic identity crisis is part of the identity.
        <br />Stumbled upon a home in a small city in the southwest corner of China in 2023.
      </p>

      <p class="paper">
        [2026.03.12] I "retired" from coding for the past few years. Recently checking what's this whole AI thing about,
        only to realise that coding is a bit like riding a bike. The body remembers. And boy has it become 
        a lot more fun since I left! Feel like a superhero who discovered a whole new superpower
        when coming out of her retirement. Like Rambo. Or Wonder Woman. Like running up the mountain with
        a pair of Chinese robot legs.
      </p>

      <h2 class="paper">Find me on</h2>

      <ul class="paper">
        <li><a href="https://kunmingwalk.com/" target="_blank">Kunming Walk for walking tours I run in Kunming, Yunnan, China</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://thenoodlejar.substack.com/" target="_blank">Substack: the Noodle Jar</a> for my semi-serious semi-literary writing</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.instagram.com/wheres.dioni/" target="_blank">@wheres.dioni</a> for occasional silly pics and stories</li> and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/kunmingwalk/" target="_blank">@kunmingwalk for why I stay in Kunming</a>
        <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/dionizhong/" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a> for my resume</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/dionizh" target="_blank">GitHub</a> for my code</li>
      </ul>

      <!--h2 class="paper">Features</h2>

      <ul class="paper">
        <li>Clean, minimal layout powered by Astro</li>
        <li>Sketch‑style UI using PaperCSS</li>
        <li>MDX support for rich content</li>
        <li>RSS and Sitemap integrations included</li>
        <li>Image optimization via Sharp</li>
        <li>Built‑in form handling through Fabform.io</li>
      </ul-->

      <!--h2 class="paper">Getting Started</h2>

      <p class="paper">
        To begin customizing this template, edit the files inside the <code>src</code> directory.
        The structure is intentionally simple, making it easy to adapt the layout, add pages,
        or integrate additional Astro features.
      </p>

      <ul class="paper">
        <li>Modify this page at <code>src/pages/index.astro</code></li>
        <li>Add new routes inside <code>src/pages/</code></li>
        <li>Update global settings in <code>src/consts.ts</code></li>
        <li>Extend layouts or components as needed</li>
      </ul-->

      <p class="paper text-center">
        <Image src={whiterabbit} alt="White Rabbit" width={481} height={494} class="paper" style="display: block; margin: 0 auto;" />
      </p>

      <p class="paper text-center">
        Fun fact: meexia (short for meecharixia) is a name of a character I 
        created when I was 20yo. My drawing of her gave me a scholarship to do
        a game dev program in Canada, and paved the way for the rest of my career in games 
        and VFX for movies.
      </p>

    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

